Turkey Gets Two Offers for Ankara Train Terminal, Star Reports

-- B y   S t e v e   B r y a n t
-- 
2011-03-03T06:17:41Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-03/turkey-gets-two-offers-for-ankara-train-terminal-star-reports.html
  Turkey ’s state rail authority got
two bids from groups to build a new fast train terminal in
Ankara, Star newspaper reported.  The offers came from a consortium of Limak Holding and
India’s GMR Infrastructure, and from a group of Ictas and Cengiz
Insaat, the newspaper said. The rail authority is evaluating the
two offers, it said citing deputy head Isa Apaydin.  Click here for web link  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
